description: BusyBox v1.01 component detected, compiled on March 24, 2014. Although no directly matching CVEs were found for version 1.01, BusyBox has historically contained multiple critical vulnerabilities (CVSS 9.8+) including command injection and buffer overflow risks. It is recommended to upgrade to the latest version.
Detected iptables-related libraries (libip4tc/libip6tc version 0.0.0) used for network packet filtering. The incomplete version information of these libraries may pose network-related security risks.
Custom library libmsglog.so detected, with no version information. Custom components require special attention; it is recommended to verify their functionality and update sources.
